JML webpages:
  http://www.eecs.ucf.edu/~leavens/JML/
  ftp://ftp.cs.iastate.edu/pub/leavens/JML/
  http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=65346

To get the "Common" tools:

# To set this variable, see "jmlspecs" part of
# http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=65346
# 5.6_rc4 is dated 3/2009, and is most recent as of 9/2009
VER=5.6_rc4
PKG=JML.$VER
# cd $pag/software/pkg
cd ~/tmp
wget http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/jmlspecs/jmlspecs/$VER/$PKG.tar.gz
# The following creates a "JML" directory
rm -f JML
tar xzf $PKG.tar.gz
mv JML $PKG
ln -s $PKG JML

# If I just want to examine the annotations, see:
#   ~/tmp/JML/specs/
# If I want to run it, read on.

# Now, read file JML/README.html.
# The below are from that.

## Only needed once ever.  This helps jmldoc find tools.jar.
# Do this first, to warm up the sudo cache.
sudo date
# jmldoc needs to find lib/tools.jar in jre/lib/ext.
cd ~/java/jdk/
(cd jre/lib/ext; sudo ln -s ../../../lib/tools.jar)
cd ~/java/jdk-1.4/
(cd jre/lib/ext; sudo ln -s ../../../lib/tools.jar)


# Myseriously, this does not work.  I don't understand this.
mkdir $pag/software/pkg/JML/install
JMLDIR=$pag/software/pkg/JML INSTALLDIR=$pag/software/pkg/JML/install JDKTOOLS=$pag/software/pkg/jdk-1.4/lib/tools.jar JML/bin/Install-JML-Scripts

## Only (really) needs to be done when new programs/man pages appear in JML.
# Symbolic link everything in $pag/software/pkg/JML/install/bin to $pag/software/bin
# Symbolic link everything in $pag/software/pkg/JML/install/man/man1 to $pag/software/man/man1

----------------

To build:

cd /g2/users/mernst/java/JML/edu/iastate/cs/jml/docs/prelimdesign/
make -k -f GMakefile


